Transient is the debut EP of Nigerian EDM producer “Cryomatic.” The project explores the euphoric world of dance music from Africa like never before. Fusing the groovy vibes of Afro-house with uplifting rhythms of Progressive House and the catchy bounce of Complextro. Transient captures an audio picture of soulful melodies perfectly bonded with upbeat sounds. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1176149 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Transient-tracklist-598x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" /> Created in collaboration with vocalists from Nigeria, Kenya & the USA, two continents are united on this project. Pushing the theme of hope and happiness especially in dark days because nothing is permanent. The EP features Celeste Ojatula, Eclipse Nkasi, Nanya Ijeh, T.O.D, Bire, David Garland, Tryenyse Jones & 10Ten and was produced by Eclipse Nkasi. To listen, click here